/wiki/Jos\u00e9_del_Solar: José Guillermo del Solar Alvarez-Calderón ( born 28 November 1967 ) is a Peruvian retired footballer who played as a defensive midfielder , and the manager of Club Deportivo Universidad César Vallejo . During his playing career , spent in four countries - mainly in Spain , where he amassed La Liga totals of 149 matches and ten goals during six seasons - he was nicknamed Chemo . He started and finished it at Universitario . Del Solar as a Peruvian international for 15 years . He started working as a manager in 2005 , also being in charge of the national team late into the decade .
/wiki/Roberto_Holsen: Roberto Carlos Holsen Alvarado ( born 10 August 1976 in Callao ) is a retired Peruvian footballer who last played for Juan Aurich .
/wiki/\u00d3scar_Ib\u00e1\u00f1ez: Óscar Manuel Ibáñez Holzmann ( born 8 August 1967 in Roque Sáenz Peña , Argentina ) is a Peruvian football goalkeeper , who made his debut for the national team on 18 April 1998 . Since then he obtained 50 caps , with the last match being on 30 March 2005 . He has been one of the four to have played at least 500 games in the Peruvian First Division . He is of Volga German descent .
/wiki/Roberto_Palacios: Roberto Carlos Palacios Mestas ( born December 28 , 1972 ) is a Peruvian retired footballer who played as a midfielder . Palacios is Peru 's record cap holder and played most of his career for Sporting Cristal , which was the team he started his career and later retired with at the end of the 2011 season .
/wiki/Miguel_Rebosio: César Miguel Rebosio Compans ( born 20 October 1976 in Lima ) is a Peruvian retired footballer who played as a defender .
/wiki/Juan_Reynoso_Guzm\u00e1n: Juan Máximo Reynoso Guzmán ( born December 28 , 1969 in Lima ) is a retired Peruvian footballer , and a current manager of Puebla .
/wiki/Jorge_Soto_(footballer): Jorge Antonio Soto Gómez ( born 27 October 1971 in Lima ) is a retired Peruvian footballer . He is also the brother of footballers José Soto and Giancarlo Soto .
